## What to Look At in Each Tool

### Kubernetes Dashboard

- **Cluster → Nodes** — all 3 nodes, CPU and memory per node
- **Workloads → Pods** — all 31 pods across all namespaces, live status
- **Workloads → Deployments** — nginx showing 2/2 replicas
- **Click any pod → Logs** — live log stream directly in the browser

### Prometheus

Try these queries in the expression bar:

```promql
# Everything being monitored — should all return 1 (up)
up

# Available memory per node in bytes
node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes

# CPU usage percentage per node
100 - (avg by(instance) (rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m])) * 100)
```

### Grafana

The Helm chart pre-loads a full set of dashboards. The most useful ones:

- **Kubernetes / Compute Resources / Cluster** — whole cluster CPU and memory at a glance
- **Kubernetes / Compute Resources / Node** — drill into a single node
- **Node Exporter / Nodes** — OS-level metrics: disk, network, system load

